{"key":"processedPost-12818537","value":{"id":12818537,"first":12817964,"last":12818671,"when":1277758407,"utime":"06/28/10 11:53 PM","content":"With quart jars, it's fine for the water to come an inch or two up the jars.&nbsp; You want to put your stove on high, and have the weight off for the first few minutes after steam begins escaping.&nbsp; This is to get all the air out of the PC and replace it with steam.&nbsp; After several minutes, put the weight on and when pressure reaches 15 psi, reduce the stove burner to the minimum setting that will maintain pressure.<br /><br />Doing the above, your 23 quart PC won't run out of water within five or six hours.&nbsp; The only people who run out of water have done so by leaving the stove burner too high during the entire cycle, and the water boils off because the excess pressure must be vented by the rattling weight.<br />RR","title":"Re: Rye berries ready to PC, pics & questions"}}